    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AnimationSimulatorUI
    SimulatorUI is a JavaFX Canvas-based visualization component that displays a real-time simulation of a customer queue management system with multiple service points.
    ApplicationAsCustomer
    Represents a customer application in the simulation.
    ApplicationLog
    Represents a log entry for an application within the simulation.
    ArrivalProcess
    Represents the arrival process in a discrete-event simulation.
    Bernoulli
    A random number generator based on the Bernoulli distribution.
    Beta
    A random number generator based on the beta distribution.
    BetaPrime
    A random number generator based on the beta prime distribution.
    Binomial
    A random number generator based on the Binomial distribution.
    Cauchy
    A random number generator based on the Cauchy distribution.
    ChiSquare
    A random number generator based on the Chi-Square distribution.
    Clock
    Singleton class representing the simulation clock.
    ContinuousGenerator
    A continuous generator provides a double value according to the distribution it relies on.
    Controller
    Controller serves as the intermediary between the simulation model and the user interface, implementing the Controller component of the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture.
    DiscreteGenerator
    A continuous generator provides a long value according to the distribution it relies on.
    DistConfig
    Entity class representing a distribution configuration for simulation runs.
    DistributionConfig
    Represents the configuration of a probability distribution used in the simulation.
    Distributions
    offers several discrete and continuous distributions all seeded by a common well-spaced pseudo random number generator (PRNG).
    Engine
    Abstract base class for the simulation engine.
    Erlang
    A random number generator based on the Erlang distribution.
    Event
    Represents a scheduled event within the simulation.
    EventList
    Maintains a prioritized list of future simulation events.
    EventType
    Represents the different types of events that can occur in the visa/immigration application processing simulation.
    FDistribution
    A random number generator based on the F-distribution.
    Gamma
    A random number generator based on the normal distribution.
    Generator
    A generic Generator class which delegates its Seedable ability to a Distributions object.
    Geometric
    A random number generator based on the geometric distribution.
    HomeController
    HomeController manages the main simulation configuration screen where users can configure and launch new simulations or review previous simulation runs.
    HomeView
    HomeView represents the main entry point and home screen of the Visa Application Processing Simulator application.
    IControllerMtoV
    IControllerMtoV defines the interface for communication from the Model to the View through the Controller in the MVC architecture.
    IControllerVtoM
    IControllerVtoM defines the interface for communication from the View to the Model through the Controller in the MVC architecture.
    IEngine
    Defines the core control interface for the simulation engine.
    IEventType
    Marker interface representing the type of simulation event.
    Invgamma
    A random number generator based on the invgamma distribution.
    ISimulatorUI
    ISimulatorUI defines the interface between the Controller and the UI layer in an MVC architecture for a queue simulation system.
    IVisualisation
    IVisualisation defines the interface for visualizing a queue simulation system.
    Logistic
    A random number generator based on the logistic distribution.
    LogNormal
    A random number generator based on the lognormal distribution.
    Main
    Entry point of the simulation application.
    MariaDbJpaConnection
    Utility class for managing JPA connections to a MariaDB database.
    MetaGenerator
    A class which allows for automatically parsing a distribution implementation and generate a class inheriting from Generator accordingly.
    MyEngine
    The MyEngine class defines the main simulation logic for the visa application processing system.
    Negexp
    A random number generator based on the negexp distribution.
    Normal
    A random number generator based on the normal distribution.
    ParameterException
    Error thrown when a distribution is passed incorrect parameters.
    Pareto
    A random number generator based on the pareto distribution.
    Pascal
    A random number generator based on the pascal distribution.
    Poisson
    A random number generator based on the poisson distribution.
    RandomGenerator
    A random number generator producing pseudorandom numbers based on the value of a specific seed.
    ResultsController
    Controller for the results view in the Visa Application Processing Simulator.
    ResultView
    Loads and displays the results view for the Visa Application Processing Simulator.
    Seedable
    represents classes which has a seed
    SeedGenerator
    A SeedGenerator is a DiscreteGenerator which produces well-spaced seeds according to its spacing attribute.
    ServicePoint
    Represents a service point in the simulation, managing a queue of applications, service processing, and performance metrics.
    SimulationController
    SimulationController manages the simulation execution screen, providing real-time monitoring and control of the running simulation.
    SimulationRun
    Represents a simulation run in the system.
    SimulationRunDao
    Data Access Object for SimulationRun and its related entities.
    SimulationView
    SimulationView manages the display of the simulation execution screen where users monitor and control a running simulation.
    SPResult
    Represents the result data for a service point in the simulation.
    Trace
    Utility class for managing trace-level logging within the simulation framework.
    Trace.Level
    Defines available levels of tracing detail.
    Tstudent
    A random number generator based on the tstudent distribution.
    Uniform
    A random number generator based on the uniform distribution.
    Weibull
    A random number generator based on the weibull distribution.
